OBJECTIVE
  learn how to test hidden or unexpected URL parameters using Burp Suite Repeater and observe how the server responds.
  TOOLS USED
  -Firefox
  -BurpSuite
  httpbin.org
  PRATICE URLs
  -https://httpbin.org/get?name=Emunah
WHAT I DID
  1. opened the practice URL in Firefox
  Turned Burpsuite Intercept ON.
  Refreshed the page to capture the request.
  sent the request to repeater.
  modified the original request by adding extra parameters.
  TESTED
  -debug=true
  -&admin=true
  -&debug=true&test=1
  sent the modified requests in repeater.
  checked the JSON responce under "args" section of the response.
  example:
  -original
  -?name=emunah
  -modified:
  -?name=emunah&admin=true
  Response showed both:
-name
-admin
  WHAT I LEARNED
  HIDDEN PARAMETER DISCOVERY
  adding extra parameters to a request to see if the server accepts them or changes behaviour.
  MULTIPLE PARAMETER TESTING
  Testing more then one parameter at once to observe how the application processes user input.
  IMPORTANT LESSON
  A server accepting a parameter does not automatically mean there is a vulnerability
  it only means the parameter is being processed and may deserve deeper testing.
  SECURITY MINDSET
  This kind of testing helps identify:
  -hidden functionality
  -debug parameter
  -weak input validation
  -access control issues
  -potential IDOR-style logic flaws
  REFLECTION
  today i practiced thinking like a bug hunter;
Capture - modify - send - compare
